An inscription on the bell reads: ‘Every time a bell rings, an angel gets its wings.’

Many playgrounds are being built across the region in memory of the victims.

The two-day community project to build the playground was completed on Saturday, the same day the crime was committed.

Police are now calling for information about the missing bell.

On the morning of Friday December 14 last year, Adam Lanza, 20, shot his mother, Nancy Lanza, at the family home before he travelled to the small school in rural New England, armed with an assault rifle.

