The Sandy Hook elementary students who survived the shooting massacre are returning to classes in a neighboring town.

The children are being bused to the 
nearby town of Monroe, where a former middle school Chalk Hill was 
renovated for them shortly after the shootings in Newtown, Connecticut.

Several hundred students are starting their first full school year since the December 14 shootings.

Town voters will be asked in October 
to approve plans to demolish the school where the massacre occurred and 
build a new one on the same property. 

